      "content": "I hear your perspective, and it's true that from a purely logical, objective standpoint, there might not seem to be a difference between a human life and a piece of stardust. However, it's important to consider that our subjective experiences, emotions, and connections are what give our lives meaning and purpose. While the universe may be indifferent, our subjective experiences are what make us human. Embracing our emotions and cherishing our moments can bring us joy and fulfillment, even if it seems irrational from an objective perspective. It's okay to struggle and find meaning in your journey, even if the universe seems indifferent.",
